---
title: Turkey, Sweet Potato & Kale Tacos with Black Beans, Crispy Fried Onions, Lime Drizzle & Guacamole
description: What are sweet potatoes doing in a taco, you ask? Everything, we say! These tasty tubers are the perfect way to make Tex-Mex night meatless. You’ll season them with our Mexican spice blend and roast them until tender and lightly crisped. Spread warm tortillas with guacamole, add saucy, savory sautéed kale and black beans, load in the sweet potatoes, then bring on the toppings! A drizzle of creamy vegan lime mayonnaise and sprinkle of crispy fried onions add brightness and crunch for “perfect bites” all the way through.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6553cac74ad73d5e5556caf9-59ad9f45.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/655521661e449ffa962aec1b.pdf
cuisine: Central America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/turkey-sweet-potato-kale-tacos-655521661e449ffa962aec1b
nutrition:
  calories: 1220 kcal
  fat: 52 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 127 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 50 g
  fiber: 18 g
  sodium: 1950 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and quarter @sweet potatoes{2} lengthwise; cut into ½-inch-thick quarter-moons.
Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%oz}; chop into bite-size pieces.
Drain and rinse @black beans{1}; transfer to a #large bowl{} and mash about half
the beans, leaving some whole. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{3%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add @ground turkey{10%oz} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; cook, stirring
frequently, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat;
transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Toss sweet potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil,
@Mexican spice blend{1/2%tbsp}, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Roast on top
rack until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan (for 4 servings, work in two
batches or use two large pans) over medium-high heat. Add kale, beans,
@mushroom stock concentrate{2}, @garlic powder{1%tsp},
@Mexican spice blend{1/2%tbsp}, and ¼ cup water (1/3 cup for 4). Cook, stirring
occasionally, until liquid has slightly reduced and kale is wilted,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in juice from one lime wedge (two wedges for 4). Season
with a pinch of salt and pepper to taste.

> Use pan used for chicken or turkey here. Once kale is wilted, stir in chicken
or turkey along with lime juice.

While veggies cook, in a #small bowl{}, combine @vegan mayonnaise{2%tbsp} with
juice from one lime wedge (two wedges for 4 servings) and as much lime zest as
you like.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, about ~{30%seconds}.

Spread a thin layer of @guacamole{4%tbsp} on tortillas. Fill with kale and bean
mixture and sweet potatoes. Spoon lime drizzle over top and garnish with
@crispy fried onions{1}.

Divide tacos between plates and serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.